## What Does NOT Get Generated

- Interactive exercises (fill_blank, dropdown, drag, etc.)
- Cards with `disableTts: true`
- Exercises in per-lesson exclude lists (e.g., workbook exercises)

## Speaker Voice Map (Dialogues)

| Speaker | Voice |
|---|---|
| РҡР»РёРөРҪСӮ | Female (Achernar) |
| РҹСҖРҫРҙР°РІР°СҮ | Male (Charon) |
| Fallback | Alternating by line index (even=female, odd=male) |

### Explicit `voiceGender` on dialogue lines (recommended)

In `exercises.ts`, each dialogue line may set `voiceGender: 'male' | 'female'` (TTS only; not shown in the UI). When set, it overrides the fallback alternation so a **male** line uses Charon and a **female** line uses Achernar.

**Two women / two men in a row:** the generator uses the **same** preset throughout (Achernar or Charon) вҖ” no second вҖһnamed speakerвҖң timbre (legacy Despina/Achird disabled).

When adding new lessons with different speakers, update `SPEAKER_VOICE_MAP` in [generate-tts.ts](mdc:scripts/generate-tts.ts) and/or add `voiceGender` on lines where roles are clear.

### Playback in the UI
The [Dialogues.tsx](mdc:src/components/exercises/Dialogues.tsx) component gives every dialogue exercise **two** controls for free:
- **Per-line click** вҖ” plays a single MP3.
- **Per-section "РЎР»СғСҲР°Р№ / Listen" button** вҖ” plays all lines in the section back-to-back with a 350 ms gap (red "РЎРҝСҖРё / Stop" while active).

Both modes rely on the same `dialogues/{exerciseId}-{sectionId}-line-{i}.mp3` files, so just running `npm run tts:generate -- --lesson XX --model gemini` is enough вҖ” no extra audio assets needed. See also the `exercise-ui` rule.

## Text Cleaning

Two cleaning functions exist:
- **`cleanForGeminiTTS()`** (Gemini): Light touch вҖ” strips leading dashes, removes parenthetical labels
- **`cleanForTTS()`** (Chirp): Aggressive вҖ” converts slashes/dashes to commas, removes exclamation marks, strips parentheses

## Content Rules for TTS Quality

These rules in **content files** directly affect audio quality:
- **Numbers as words** in `listeningText`, `reading_text.paragraphs`, **AND every `grammar_examples.examples[].text/subtext` that will be TTS-read** вҖ” write вҖһСҒРөРҙРөРјРҙРөСҒРөСӮ Рё СҲРөСҒСӮ" not вҖһ76", вҖһРҙРөСҒРөСӮ СҮР°СҒР°" not вҖһ10:00". TTS reads digits unnaturally. If display must show digits (e.g. вҖһР—Р°РәСғСҒРІР°Рј РҝСҖРөРҙРё 10:00 СҮР°СҒР°."), set `ttsText: 'Р—Р°РәСғСҒРІР°Рј РҝСҖРөРҙРё РҙРөСҒРөСӮ СҮР°СҒР°.'` so display stays unchanged but audio is clean.
- **Period, not dash** between sums вҖ” `'Р РөСҒСӮРҫСӮРҫ. Р§РөСӮРёСҖРё РөРІСҖРҫ.'` not `'Р РөСҒСӮРҫСӮРҫ вҖ” СҮРөСӮРёСҖРё РөРІСҖРҫ.'`. Dashes confuse pacing.
- **No `=` sign in TTS text** вҖ” TTS reads `=` as вҖһСҖР°РІРҪРҫ" / вҖһСҖР°РІРҪСҸРө СҒРө РҪР°". The script auto-replaces `=` вҶ’ `,` in `cleanForGeminiTTS()`, but prefer to write commas directly in content. For `grammar_examples` cards where a visual `=` is desired (e.g. вҖһ30 РјРёРҪСғСӮРё = РҝРҫР»РҫРІРёРҪР°"), set `ttsText: '30 РјРёРҪСғСӮРё, РҝРҫР»РҫРІРёРҪР°.'` to keep display + clean audio.
- **No `/` between alternatives in TTS** вҖ” write вҖһРұРөР·, Рё" instead of вҖһР‘Р•Р— / Рҳ"; вҖһРјРёРҪСғСӮРё РҝСҖРөРҙРё, СҒР»РөРҙ СҮР°СҒР°" instead of вҖһРјРёРҪСғСӮРё РҝСҖРөРҙРё / СҒР»РөРҙ СҮР°СҒР°". Slashes break pacing. Use `ttsText` to override.
- **No markdown** in text fields вҖ” TTS reads asterisks, brackets etc. Keep text clean. (РҳР·РәР»СҺСҮРөРҪРёРө: `grammar_table.cells` РјРҫР¶Рө РҙР° РҝРҫР»Р·РІР° `**bold**` Р·Р° СғРҙРөРұРөР»СҸРІР°РҪРө РҪР° РҫРәРҫРҪСҮР°РҪРёСҸ вҖ” markdown СҒРө РҝСҖРөРјР°С…РІР° РҝСҖРөРҙРё TTS.)
- **voiceGender on every dialogue line** where the speaker's gender is clear (male/female). Fallback alternation works but explicit is better.
- **Voice alternation rule (AchernarвҶ”Despina, CharonвҶ”Achird)** вҖ” the script alternates between primary and ALT voices ONLY for **consecutive same-gender lines within the same dialogue section** (clear case of two characters of the same gender in conversation). For sections where genders alternate (Рҗ=Р¶РөРҪР° / Р‘=РјСҠР¶ by line), the same primary voice is used for all of Рҗ's lines and all of Р‘'s lines. This avoids the bug where the same character sounds like two different people across lines.
- **Problematic words** вҖ” add to `GRAMMAR_TABLE_PRO_ROWS` if a Flash-generated word sounds wrong. Examples: вҖһС…РёР»СҸРҙР°", вҖһРјРёР»РёР°СҖРҙ", вҖһРІРёРө СҖР°РұРҫСӮРёСӮРө".
- **`reading_text` СҒ РёР»СҺСҒСӮСҖР°СҶРёРё Р·Р°РҙСҠР»Р¶РёСӮРөР»РҪРҫ СҒ TTS** вҖ” Р°РәРҫ СғСҖРҫРә СҒРјРөСҒРІР° СӮРөРәСҒСӮ + РҪРҫРІРё РҙСғРјРё (РҪР°РҝСҖ. СғСҖРҫРә 3 СғРҝСҖ. 33, СғСҖРҫРә 4 СғРҝСҖ. 34/37/39/41), РІСҒСҸРәР° РәР°СҖСӮРёРҪРәР° РІ `images[]` СӮСҖСҸРұРІР° РҙР° РёРјР° `ttsWordId` + `label`. РўРҫРІР° РҝСҖРҫРёР·РІРөР¶РҙР° `words/{ttsWordId}.mp3` Рё flip-card СҒРІРёСҖРё Р·РІСғРә РҝСҖРё РәР»РёРә. Р‘Р•Р— СӮРҫРІР° РәР°СҖСӮРёРҪРәРёСӮРө РҫСҒСӮР°РІР°СӮ РұРөР· Р·РІСғРә.

